        "excerpt":"1. _docs - ğŸ“ Create New Documentation   To create new documentation, simply add a new Markdown file.  For example: 04-how-to-install-awx.md   --- title: |          How to Install Ansible AWX ğŸš€ &lt;br&gt;         ![Ansible](https://img.shields.io/badge/ansible-automation-red)         ![Ansible Tower](https://img.shields.io/badge/ansible--tower-management--ui-blue)         ![Ansible AWX](https://img.shields.io/badge/ansible--awx-open--source--ui-green)  permalink: /docs/how-to-install-awx/ excerpt: \"This guide explains how to install Ansible AWX on RHEL 9.\" last_modified_at: 2025-02-08T21:36:18-04:00 toc: true ---  # ğŸš€ How to Install AWX on RHEL 9   ...   ğŸ”— Linking Documentation to docs.md  To add a link to this documentation in docs.md, edit the following section:     - image_path: /assets/pictures/16.png     alt: \"Automation with Red Hat Ansible ğŸ¤–\"     title: \"Automation with Red Hat Ansible ğŸ¤–\"     excerpt: \"Best practices for system maintenance and optimization.\"     url: \"/docs/how-to-install-awx\"     btn_class: \"btn--primary\"     btn_label: \"Learn More\"     2. _data - ğŸ“Œ Edit Navbar for Documentation   To display the documentation link in the navigation menu, edit navigation.yml:     - title: Red Hat Ansible ğŸ¤–     children:       - title: \"How to Install AWX\"         url: /docs/how-to-install-awx     3. _posts - ğŸ“° Create a Blog Post   If you want to publish a portfolio or blog post, navigate to the _posts directory and create a new Markdown file, e.g., 2025-02-08-new-post-miftah.md   --- title: \"ğŸš€ New Post: Miftah &amp; Red Hat\" categories:   - redhat tags:   - content   - css   - edge case   - lists   - markup ---  Hi, Miftah! Welcome to my latest blog post on **Red Hat technologies**! ğŸš€     4. _&lt;projects&gt; - ğŸš€ Publish a Project   To create a new project experience, create a directory inside your repository and add a Markdown file.   Example: Creating a Project Directory  cd miftah-ahmad-choiri.github.io mkdir _relocation vi _relocation/example.md   Example Project File (example.md)  --- title: \"Pending Execution\" excerpt: \"A tabby is any domestic cat that has a coat featuring distinctive stripes, dots, lines, or swirling patterns, usually with a mark resembling an 'M' on its forehead.\" ---  &gt; A tabby is any domestic cat that has a coat featuring distinctive stripes, dots, lines, or swirling patterns, usually together with a mark resembling an 'M' on its forehead.   &gt;   &gt; ğŸ± Tabbies are sometimes mistakenly thought to be a breed, but in reality, the tabby pattern is found in many cat breeds and mixed-breed populations.   &gt;   &gt; &lt;cite&gt;â€” From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia&lt;/cite&gt;   ğŸ‰ Once added, the project will automatically appear in the My Projects list under the Relocation category.     âœ… Summary     ğŸ“„ Documentation: Add a Markdown file in _docs   ğŸ“Œ Navbar Links: Edit navigation.yml in _data   ğŸ“° Blog Posts: Add new files in _posts   ğŸš€ Projects: Create directories inside _&lt;projects&gt;   Letâ€™s keep building awesome content! ğŸš€ğŸ”¥  ","categories": [],
